conversation_events.text:
I am thinking...: The nghttp3 library has `nghttp3_conn_submit_priority_update` for sending PRIORITY_UPDATE frames. The API signature is:
```c
int nghttp3_conn_submit_priority_update(nghttp3_conn *conn, int64_t stream_id, const nghttp3_pri *pri);
```

Where `nghttp3_pri` is:
```c
typedef struct nghttp3_pri {
  uint32_t urgency;
  int incremental;
} nghttp3_pri;
```

This is the standard nghttp3 API for RFC 9218 priority. Let me create the curl_ngtcp2.c patch that adds priority setting after `nghttp3_conn_submit_request`.

Running command: cat > /workspace/src/tool_getparam.c << 'EOF'
  {"09",  "http0.9",                 ARG_BOOL},
  {"0a",  "proxy-http2",             ARG_BOOL},
  {"0b",  "h3-priority",             ARG_STRING},

      case 'b': /* --h3-priority */
        /* Set HTTP/3 stream priority per RFC 9218 Extensible Priorities */
        if(!feature_http3)
          return PARAM_LIBCURL_DOESNT_SUPPORT;
        GetStr(&config->h3_priority, nextarg);
        break;
EOF

